news.title: Telangana government to set up two new IT parks near Hyderabad
news.para: Telangana IT & industries minister D Sridhar Babu also said that with industries facing challenges in acquiring land, the govt plans to come up with a dedicated land allocation policy that will allocate land based on the scale of investment and the number of jobs to be created.

news.title: Gharkul beneficiaries to get priority under PMAY: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Rural Development Minister Shri. Gore said that Prime Minister Narendra Modi is insistent that everyone in the country should get a house of their right.

news.title: Aditya Birla Housing Finance raises Rs 830 crore fund from IFC
news.para: The funds raised through IFC's investment will be utilised to address critical gaps by providing housing loans to low-income and middle-income groups, with a particular focus on encouraging homeownership among women, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Bihar RERA issues arrest warrants against three builders
news.para: The order was passed to recover an amount of about Rs 21 lakh from the builders, which is to be paid to three aggrieved home buyers, an official said.

news.title: Karnataka RERA recovers only Rs 91 crore of Rs 758.85 crore penalties from builders
news.para: According to K-RERA’s latest report, as of December 31, 2024, the authority has collected just 12% of the dues from builders, while 88% remains to be recovered.

news.title: Budget 2025: Real estate sector seeks GST reforms and tax incentives to boost growth
news.para: As Union Budget 2025 approaches, real estate stakeholders are urging the government to introduce key reforms, particularly in GST rationalization and tax benefits for homebuyers. Industry leaders believe these measures will drive housing demand, improve affordability, and support economic growth.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP tells developers to expedite affordable housing projects
news.para: DTPC reviewed the status of 55 ongoing projects, of which 40 were found to be progressing on time while around 15 were running behind schedule, causing inconvenience to homebuyers.

news.title: Budget 2025: Experts demand industry recognition for co-working and increased infrastructure investments
news.para: Real estate experts are advocating for formal industry recognition of the coworking sector and increased infrastructure investments in Union Budget 2025. These measures, they believe, will drive economic growth and encourage innovation in the evolving commercial real estate landscape.

news.title: Budget 2025: Government should introduce reforms in affordable housing
news.para: We feel reforms should be undertaken under affordable housing units and projects, introducing credit guarantee schemes, modifying income tax and GST provisions, and streamlining stamp duty policies.

news.title: Maharashtra govt likely to hike ready reckoner rates by 10% from April 1: Officials
news.para: RR rate is the state govt's assessment of property value, based on which stamp duty and registration charges are levied. The rate is primarily used for valuation of properties.

news.title: Budget 2025: Eliminate GST on affordable housing
news.para: The upcoming budget is seen as a golden opportunity to provide targeted relief, fostering housing demand and facilitating the seamless growth of infrastructure projects.

news.title: Norway's sovereign wealth fund posts record $222 billion annual profit on tech boom
news.para: "The American technology stocks in particular performed very well," Nicolai Tangen, CEO of Norges Bank Investment Management (NBIM), the fund's operator, said in a statement.

news.title: Infra. Market leases eight-storey office tower from Ekatva Group in Thane
news.para: Around 70,000 sq ft has been leased to the company. Infra.Market and its group companies will register the first three floors in January 2025 and the remaining five in March 2025.

news.title: Mumbai civic body to upgrade its system to track encroachments
news.para: Citizens will also be able to know if a particular building or flat has carried out unauthorised construction, as the system will integrate existing systems of various BMC depts on a single platform and enable sharing of data and coordination between depts.

news.title: G Square plans to invest Rs 1,000 crore in next two years
news.para: G Square will be expanding its existing presence in Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, and Telangana.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises posts net profit of Rs 235.52 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Brigade Enterprises' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,529.68 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 26.61 per cent from Rs 1,208.18 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces posts net profit of Rs 50.18 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 215.47 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 149.33 per cent from Rs 86.42 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government announces 145 crore waiver on Tidco loans
news.para: Subsequently, the APTidco corporation aims to complete the 4,500 pending housing complexes in the Jakkampudi housing layout and hand them over to the beneficiaries at the earliest.

news.title: Embassy REIT's net operating income up 9% to Rs 829 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services (EOPMSPL), manager to Embassy Office Parks REIT (Embassy REIT), declared distributions of Rs 5,592.57 million/Rs 5.90 per unit for the quarter ended December 31, 2024.
